SystemAudioSource.handleAudioSampleBuffer: replaced CMTimeGetSeconds(pts)*1e9 with HostClock.nowNanos() for the capture timestamp. Root cause of the 100% dropPast symptom: SCStream audio PTS lives in CMClockGetHostTimeClock() which is not bit-identical to mach_absolute_time on every macOS configuration, so the host's stamped hostTimeNanos was in a different clock domain than what TimeSync (calibrated via HostClock.nowNanos on both sides) could translate. Translated localCaptureNanos consistently landed in the past, scheduler rejected every packet. Trading ~5-10ms of true-capture-instant precision for a clock-domain guarantee, well inside our 35ms latency budget.